    <h2 id="faq">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Is the Herman Miller Aeron better than the Steelcase Gesture?</summary>
        <p>The Aeron is better for warm environments and people who want a breathable, suspended mesh seat with iconic design and a 12-year warranty. The Gesture is better for people who change posture often and move between phones, tablets, and laptops, because its 360-degree armrests track your arms through nearly any position.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Which chair is better for back pain, the Aeron or the Gesture?</summary>
        <p>The Aeron with PostureFit SL is the stronger choice for lower-back pain because it stabilizes the pelvis and supports the lumbar curve directly. The Gesture's live back adjusts to your spine as you recline, which helps people who shift positions throughout the day, but its lumbar support is less targeted than the Aeron's PostureFit.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is the Herman Miller Aeron worth the higher price over the Steelcase Gesture?</summary>
        <p>If breathability, premium build, and long-term resale value matter most, the Aeron's $1,495 price is justified by its 12-year warranty and durability. If budget and armrest flexibility matter more, the Gesture at $979 delivers comparable ergonomics for about $500 less. Both are excellent 10-plus-year investments.</p>
      </details>
    </div>

